 :tx/rationale "CORR-3: Index synchronization depends on programmer discipline — 3 divergent insertion paths [HIGH, from FULL_AUDIT F-INV-003]. Five secondary indexes + MaterializedViews are maintained by index_datom() in store.rs, but there is no compile-time enforcement that this call happens for every datom insertion. Four insertion paths exist: (1) genesis() calls views.observe_datom() but NOT index_datom() — indexes rebuilt in from_datoms(). (2) from_datoms() calls views.observe_datom() then rebuilds indexes separately. (3) apply_tx() calls index_datom() per datom — the correct path. (4) apply_datoms() rebuilds everything from scratch. Paths 1 and 2 use observe_datom() directly, bypassing index_datom(). MaterializedViews and index paths are not unified. SOLUTION: Make index_datom() the sole function that updates BOTH indexes AND MaterializedViews. Remove the separate observe_datom() method. All paths (genesis, from_datoms, apply_tx, apply_datoms) call index_datom. VERIFICATION: grep -n observe_datom store.rs returns only definition and calls from index_datom. All existing tests pass. DEPENDENCIES: Prerequisite for CORR-1 (LIVE view fix) — unified path ensures LIVE correction applies everywhere. Interacts with AUDIT-PERF-2 (merge rebuild uses apply_datoms path)."
